# snarOS

snarOS is a from-scratch operating system written in C and Assembly,
built for learning, research, and long-term independent OS development.

## Version
snarOS v1.0

## Supported Architecture
- x86_64
- UEFI boot

## Features
- UEFI bootloader
- 64-bit kernel
- Framebuffer text output
- Memory management (PMM + VMM)
- Kernel heap
- Interrupt handling
- Keyboard driver
- Timer driver
- RAM-based filesystem
- Interactive kernel shell

## What snarOS v1.0 is NOT
- No GUI
- No multitasking
- No networking
- No disk filesystem
- No user mode programs

These are planned for future versions.

## Build


make
./run.sh


## Philosophy
snarOS focuses on clarity, stability, and clean architecture
before adding complexity.

## Roadmap
- v2.0: multitasking
- v3.0: userspace
- v4.0: filesystem
- v5.0: GUI

## License
MIT

